          "description": "Honestly horrible. I was waiting in the waiting room for one hour, even though I made an appointment. I feel like there\u2019s no reason for that feature if you don\u2019t honor the time of the appointment or at least have a max waiting period for those who scheduled. I had to ask the receptionist how much longer and then 5 minutes later I was seen, (like they purposefully did waited till they had to see me)\n\nAfter that the experience was worse, very unorganized one nurse came to check vitals and 10 minutes another nurse said the same thing and I had to tell them it was already done. She then tested me for strep Covid and flu and said it\u2019ll be 10 minutes till the doctor comes sees me. I waited ANOTHER HOUR for him to see me. Which again I had to ask about to a nurse on the wait time and he shows up five minutes later. When he came in he stayed for a maximum of 5 minutes.\n\nDuring the meeting he explained I likely have a viral infection and I was very much being persistent on what other likelihoods of things I could have because I\u2019ve had these symptoms for over a week and keep getting worse. He then proceeds to tell me:\n\n- your cough doesn't seem that bad you haven't had it so far (he's been in the room for 5 minutes)\n\u2022 yeah if you want to fact check you can try google or Al....this was so unprofessional and rude to hear given I spent two hours to have an expert\u2019s opinion\n\u2022 I kept telling him I keep getting crusty eyes during the day (weird obv cause you wake up with them and he's like yeah that doesn't make sense (nothing else) the goes AGAIN and says well you dont have it right now so you seem fine.\n\nOverall he seemed dismissive and like he made up his mind on how to diagnose me. He also didn\u2019t introduce himself when walking in and had no bed side manner. He only checked my ears and lungs after I kept emphasizing my symptoms. The doctors name is: Herman Chiu DO based off the lab report I was given.\n\nOn top of that the receptionist said this would be covered by insurance yet I was charged $258 which I\u2019ll be calling for more details on since she said I wouldn\u2019t have to pay anything\u2026\n\nOverall this was one of the worst experiences I\u2019ve had and things clearly need to reviewed by their team on the level of professionalism for your staff.",
