          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUYDWoY9SeF8jBA_J0bPwM3CxpbBn9XdjVzz13rr4ADeiRbolQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "I actually wonder if this place should be allowed to practice medicine, the level of neglect from staff and doctors here is so shocking. The in-clinic visit itself was ok \u2014the staff on site were the minimal level of courteous, I mean the receptionist was checked out but the nurse was nice; the doctor rushed but polite.\n\nHowever, the aftercare was shocking and amounted to malpractice. The lab results seemed written by AI, misgendered me and ignored my clinical history. When I followed up with questions by phone, the work from home nurse who answered did not engage with my specific situation. Her family was shouting in the background and she did not seem interested in my problem. I had to ask her to send an email to a physician and had to dictate the question.\n\nThat earned me a return call from a second nurse. She agreed that something was amiss and at least asked me to wait and tried getting a physician to look at my results. (In most people, the results I received would be fine but given my clinical history the results were concerning and required antibiotics.) In the end, I never spoke to a doctor and was told to go back to Urgent Care!\n\nDespite the staff having my relevant clinical context in front of their eyes, my questions were never addressed in a meaningful way. Instead, I received generic, scripted responses that simply repeated what was already written in the lab report. This made it difficult to feel confident in the quality of the guidance I was receiving. I ended up going to the ER instead and I am glad I did. They immediately put me on an IV drip with antibiotics and kept shaking their heads in disbelief when I explained the stonewalling I encountered at CityMD. Please be very careful with this overly corporate, robotic operation.",
