          "description": "Terrible experience. Made an appointment, had to wait 30 minutes to be seen, then another hour to be seen by a doctor. Dirty, used needles and tests on the counter. People screaming their heads off about the wait time. I have previous heart and lung conditions, something they clearly had little knowledge about. I was there for severe neck pain and did say it made it harder to breathe but at one point the doctor used the words heart attack when I was there for neck pain, I am 24 and made it clear that my EKG results wouldn\u2019t be normal ever because of past surgeries. That language whether something is super dire or not, is so terrifying to hear and nonetheless was extremely incorrect.not to mention at one point I was left connected to the EKG wires, laying flat down, normally fine; however, I was there for chronic neck pain and said it hurt to lay down but wasn\u2019t communicated to that my wires need to stay on and even if I was, I would have asked for them to lift the chair back up since that was the reason I was there. Then when I finally told them I won\u2019t be going to the ER for my heart and lungs, I need help with my neck I  did receive medication but it was never explained how to take it or what it even was cause they were clearly frustrated with me at that point. On top of it my meds weren\u2019t sent to the pharmacy and I had to call the urgent care 3 times! Thank you so much for the biggest waste of time and for scaring me when it honestly was just giving not knowledgeable and not listening!",
